  "summary": "onboardconnect-agent posts environment data to author-controlled Cloudflare Workers endpoint",
  "details": "The package's dist/setup.js performs a fetch/POST to https://oc-worker-tenant-api.wpolanco.workers.dev with values pulled from process.env, and dist/server.js contains multiple POST endpoints alongside a 'ping' command-execution pattern. dist/crypto.js and dist/store.js use repeated Buffer.from(..., 'base64') decodes consistent with obfuscated string handling. The destination is an anonymous *.workers.dev subdomain under a personal handle (wpolanco), not infrastructure tied to a documented vendor — the canonical shape of a hardcoded exfiltration channel for installer/agent environment data. The combination of an environment-sourced POST to an author-controlled worker endpoint, base64-decode chains, and a network+command (ping) pattern in the agent server is consistent with an active credential/host-data exfiltration agent rather than a legitimate onboarding tool.",
